{
  "texts": [
    "For this work, we built a PV for each molecule that contains 53 molecular properties and considered this as a sentence with a length of 53.",
    "These properties from the RDKit python library 59 cover a wide range from simple ones, such as the number of rings and molar mass, to complex properties like solubility, TPSA, and druggability.",
    "The transformer architecture of our model considers each element of PV as a token to perform the attention mechanism, which is equivalent to regarding PV as a semi-sentence of 53 properties.",
    "Although the size of the vocabulary is more limited and their order is fixed compared to natural language, it provides much more precise and compact information about the 53 properties.",
    "One benefit of regarding PV as a language is that we do not have to collect all elements to build a valid PV."
  ]
}